{
  "text": "The Zika virus recently emerged as a major threat to global health. It is a flavivirus that depends on the activity of a viral NS2B-NS3 protease, which thus is an attractive drug target. Owing to its high sequence and structure similarity with other flaviviral NS2B-NS3 proteases, such as the West Nile virus (WNV) [CITATION_1] and dengue virus proteases, an inhibitor of the Zika virus protease could even display broad-spectrum activity against a wide range of flaviviruses [CITATION_2] .",
